  "datePublished": "2026-03-06",
  "description": "A ***style guide*** is a document that defines how writing should be done within an organization, publication, or project. It governs decisions that grammar alone does not resolve: word choice, capitalization conventions, formatting standards, tone, and voice. Its purpose is consistency — so that writing produced by different people at different times reads as if it came from one mind.",
